## Python Style Guide

### PEP 8 Compliance

This project follows [PEP 8](https://pep.python.org/pep-0008/) - Python's official style guide.

**Key Points:**
- Indentation: 4 spaces (no tabs)
{% if include_formatting %}- Line length: 88 characters (Black default){% else %}- Line length: 79 characters (PEP 8 standard){% endif +%}
- Encoding: UTF-8
- Imports: Grouped (standard library, third-party, local)

## Naming Conventions

### Variables and Functions
```python
# Good
user_name = "John"
def calculate_total():
    pass

# Bad
userName = "John"  # camelCase
def CalculateTotal():  # PascalCase for function
    pass
```

### Classes
```python
# Good
class MainWindow:
    pass

class UserProfile:
    pass

# Bad
class main_window:  # snake_case
    pass
```

### Constants
```python
# Good
MAX_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT = 30
DEFAULT_COLOR = "blue"

# Bad
max_connection_timeout = 30  # lowercase
```

### Private Methods/Variables
```python
class Example:
    def __init__(self):
        self._private_var = 10      # Single underscore: internal use
        self.__really_private = 20  # Double underscore: name mangling
    
    def _internal_method(self):
        pass
```

